A = [4, 3, 2, 6]

F(0) = (0 * 4) + (1 * 3) + (2 * 2) + (3 * 6) = 0 + 3 + 4 + 18 = 25
F(1) = (0 * 6) + (1 * 4) + (2 * 3) + (3 * 2) = 0 + 4 + 6 + 6 = 16

F(1) = F(0) - 3*A[3] + (A[0]+A[1]+A[2]) = 25 - 3*6 + 4 + 3 + 2 = 16

To find F(1) from F(0),
first you have to subtract last value during F(0) n-1 times, then you have to add all others values 1 time.

You can write it as :
F(1) = F(0) - (n-1)*A[n-1] + (sum-A[n-1])
Which can be generalized as :
F(k) = F(k-1) - (n-1)*A[n-k] + (sum - A[n-k])


class Solution {
