Observe that if an array has 5 elements [A, B, C, D, E]. 
F(0) = 0A + 1B + 2C + 3D + 4E
F(1) = 0E + 1A + 2B + 3C + 4D
F(2) = 0D + 1E + 2A + 3B + 4C

F(1) - F(0) = A + B + C + D -4E
F(2) - F(1) = A + B + C - 4D + E

Thus, the difference between iterations are
A + B + C + D + E - size * rotating element

