Just take a look at an example:
```A = [a1, a2, a3, a4], let sum = sum of all elements in A```
```val1 = 0 * a1 + 1 * a2 + 2 * a3 + 3 * a4```
```val2 = 3 * a1 + 0 * a2 + 1 * a3 + 2 * a4``` 
       ```= 4 * a1 - a1 + 1 * a2 - 1 * a2 + 2 * a3 - a3 + 3 * a4 - a4``` 
			```	= 4 * a1 + 1 * a2 + 2 * a3 + 3 * a4 - (a1 + a2 + a3 + a4) = val1 - sum + 4 * a1 ```
similarly, ```val3 = val2 - sum + 4 * a2, val4 = val3 - sum + 4 * a3```, so all possible values of rotation function ```F(k)``` can be calculated based on the previous result in ```O(1)``` time. The code is down below for reference:
```
class Solution {
    public int maxRotateFunction(int[] A) {
        if (A == null || A.length == 0) return 0;
        int sum = 0, val = 0;
        for (int i = 0; i <A.length; i++) {
            sum += A[i];
            val += i * A[i];
        }

        int max = val;
        for (int i = 1; i < A.length; i++) {
            val = val - sum + A[i - 1] * A.length;
            max = Math.max(val, max);
        }

        return max;
    }
}
```

